HEADWORD: Affamish
<hw>Af*fam"ish</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧f*f⟦acr⟧m"⟦icr⟧sh)</pr>, <pos>v. t. &
i.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>affamer</ets>, fr. L. <ets>ad</ets> +
<ets>fames</ets> hunger. See <er>Famish</er>.]</ety> <def>To afflict
with, or perish from, hunger.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
